      <biogHist id="md5-88a7da99cdd240af3ae305e934704c6b">
        <p>Forester, [1904]-  .  Reg D. Loomis joined the Alberta Forest Surveys Division, ca. 1950, after  being employed with the federal government as a forestry researcher and with International Paper  Company in New Brunswick. He was Senior Superintendent, 1953-1966, and Administrator of  Forest Management in the Alberta Department of Lands and Forests from 1966 to 1969. He retired in 1973. The province's first professional forester, he helped introduce sustained yield logging to  Alberta.</p>
      </biogHist>
